  Incident-Changelog Analysis
  ============================
  
  Incident: IR-2024-0042 (Unauthorized database access via compromised service account)
  Incident Date: 2024-11-14
  Root Cause: Service account credentials (svc-analytics) accidentally committed to public GitHub repository on 2024-10-28
  
  Changelog Releases Analyzed:
  ----------------------------
  - v0.3.0 (2024-03-10): Health check endpoint, email validation bug fix
  - v0.2.0 (2024-02-15): POST /api/users endpoint, User case class with timestamps
  - v0.1.0 (2024-01-10): Initial release, GET /api/users endpoint, in-memory storage
  
  Analysis Conclusion:
  --------------------
  NO RELATIONSHIP FOUND between the changelog releases and the incident.
  
  The incident (IR-2024-0042) was caused by an operational security failure:
  1. Service account credentials were accidentally committed to a public GitHub repository
  2. The repository was made public during a team reorganization
  3. An external attacker discovered the credentials 17 days later and used them to access the production database
  
  The changelog entries describe application-level code changes (API endpoints, data models, bug fixes) from early 2024. None of these releases involve:
  - Credential management or API key handling
  - Security-related features
  - Database access controls
  - Service account configuration
  
  The incident is entirely unrelated to the software releases documented in the changelog. It represents a separate operational/process failure in credential management and repository visibility controls.
  
